00:01:42.120 --> 00:01:44.920
it's a special time.

00:01:44.920 --> 00:01:50.799
In the following video, note how Jehovah's Provision of Food gives evidence that he wants

00:01:50.799 --> 00:01:57.250
us to enjoy life.

00:01:57.250 --> 00:02:03.620
Our tongue can detect five basic tastes.

00:02:03.620 --> 00:02:24.879
There is sweet, salty, sour, bitter, and the rich savoury taste called umami, but we

00:02:24.879 --> 00:02:33.830
enjoy not just five flavors, but possibly over a hundred thousand.

00:02:33.830 --> 00:02:35.509
How?

00:02:35.509 --> 00:02:41.030
As we chew, we also smell our food.

00:02:41.030 --> 00:02:48.189
Doing releases aromas that pass up into our nose through the back of our throat.

00:02:48.189 --> 00:03:02.000
Taste and smell then combine to make the flavors we enjoy.

00:03:02.000 --> 00:03:06.479
Our taste buds develop before we're born.

00:03:06.479 --> 00:03:14.360
As an unborn baby swallows amniotic fluid, it may taste with its mother eats, and is

00:03:14.360 --> 00:03:20.750
more likely to enjoy the same food she does.

00:03:20.750 --> 00:03:24.870
We don't eat just to survive.

00:03:24.870 --> 00:03:28.349
We love to eat.

00:03:28.349 --> 00:03:34.960
It makes us happy.

00:03:34.960 --> 00:03:45.069
The Bible says why that everyone should eat and drink and find enjoyment for all his

00:03:45.069 --> 00:03:46.069
hard work.

00:03:46.069 --> 00:03:55.919
It is the gift of God.

00:03:55.919 --> 00:04:02.400
We are made so that we must take in physical food regularly in order to survive.

00:04:02.400 --> 00:04:08.719
Yet how grateful we are that our Creator has made eating so enjoyable.

00:04:08.719 --> 00:04:17.160
That reflects the way of Jehovah, fulfilling our needs creates joy, not dread.

00:04:17.160 --> 00:04:21.639
You will not find a normal individual complaining about eating a good dinner.

00:04:21.639 --> 00:04:26.240
No, rather, it's enjoyable.

00:04:26.240 --> 00:04:33.079
Now turn with me, please, to Matthew chapter 4, and notice another vital need we have

00:04:33.079 --> 00:04:36.199
that relates to food.

00:04:36.199 --> 00:04:48.480
Matthew 4, 4, it says, it is written, man must live not on bread alone, but on every

00:04:48.480 --> 00:04:52.920
word that comes from Jehovah's mouth.

00:04:52.920 --> 00:04:58.000
We need physical food to stay alive, and we enjoy doing so.

00:04:58.000 --> 00:05:01.319
But the same is true with spiritual food.

00:05:01.319 --> 00:05:04.920
We need it to stay alive spiritually.

00:05:04.920 --> 00:05:12.160
So just as it's true with physical food, when we partake of spiritual food, we find true

00:05:12.160 --> 00:05:13.160
joy.

00:05:13.160 --> 00:05:18.600
Isn't that what Jesus said in his introduction to the Sermon on the Mount?

00:05:18.600 --> 00:05:24.319
Happy are those conscious of their spiritual need?

00:05:24.319 --> 00:05:32.600
The beauty of Jehovah's way is that he has made the satisfying of our spiritual need enjoyable.

00:05:32.600 --> 00:05:34.199
Why do we say that?

00:05:34.920 --> 00:05:42.360
Because God's word, the Bible, is written in a way that is appealing to us.

00:05:42.360 --> 00:05:46.040
In his great wisdom, he used humans to write the Bible.

00:05:46.040 --> 00:05:47.519
Think about it.

00:05:47.519 --> 00:05:52.519
If, for example, he had used angels, would they have been able to convey the emotions

00:05:52.519 --> 00:05:56.240
and feelings with a human touch?

00:05:56.240 --> 00:06:04.160
Words convey not just information, but emotion, such as fear, sorrow, and disappointment,

00:06:05.160 --> 00:06:11.160
by allowing imperfect men to choose the wording for the ideas they received through Holy Spirit.

00:06:11.160 --> 00:06:20.160
God conveyed his message with warmth, variety, and the appeal of human emotions and feelings.

00:06:20.160 --> 00:06:24.160
That makes his word appealing to us humans.

00:06:24.160 --> 00:06:32.160
In addition to that, Jehovah provides a variety of spiritual food in abundance.

00:06:33.160 --> 00:06:42.160
But taking in spiritual food requires effort just as it takes in preparing and eating a delicious meal.

00:06:42.160 --> 00:06:50.160
Rice and beans, kimchi, and Jehovah's rice each take time and effort to prepare.

00:06:50.160 --> 00:06:54.160
It takes effort to plant, cultivate, and pick watermelon.

00:06:54.160 --> 00:06:59.160
But what a joy it is to experience the results of such efforts.

00:06:59.160 --> 00:07:05.160
What can we do to make the study of God's word more enjoyable?

00:07:05.160 --> 00:07:12.160
